{"title":"AgonistaDualdeGLP-1yGIP(Tirzepatida)","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología/AgonistaDualdeGLP-1yGIP(Tirzepatida)-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Agonista Dual de GLP-1 y GIP\\N(Tirzepatida)","guid":"tmO7jmbDWZUQ9W2sPsyaWw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"0. Perlas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Paciente tipo: Adultos con DM2 no controlada con dieta y ejercicio, o con terapia convencional.","guid":"A36BFVEFxXHhLOPtFZVx2Q","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Efecto HbA1c: Reducción del 1.5-2.5% (Alto).","guid":"d1n634YSZq4WvnaAQckRUg","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Peso: Pérdida de hasta 12-15% del peso corporal.","guid":"B26fqRiUNHNpvEx9TqqJ6w","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Sobrevida general: Potencial mejora en calidad de vida y reducción de complicaciones DM2 a largo plazo.","guid":"wQRiiYuE5VYYJkBwN9xsqA","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"• Efectos pleiotrópicos: Mejora perfil lipídico, disminución de PA, reducción de inflamación.","guid":"fWUTFI5tVLtl1XVR8Ri_UQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"1. Efecto:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Receptores: GLP-1R, GIPR.","guid":"cmr3cT6BudwyM1UoMxg1Qw","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Mecanismo:","guid":"E__mY5FrEvUO5557svBnbg","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• GLP-1: Aumenta insulina, inhibe glucagón, retrasa vaciado gástrico.","guid":"AViO30tf0YEdOraGCYu_cQ","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"• GIP: Potencia insulina dependiente de glucosa, mejora sensibilidad a insulina.","guid":"sknFrJC8ZpX8_utwwQeNGg","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"7","text":"• Resultado: Mejor control glucémico, pérdida de peso, mejor perfil lipídico.","guid":"F-Fk0iSMQ2qGZ-oADq-Hgw","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"0","text":"2. Farmacología:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Absorción: Administración SC, Tmax ≈ 1 semana.","guid":"YCz5LBsPzivW4Og1BlAQPA","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"• Distribución: Unión a proteínas plasmáticas alta.","guid":"eAG_v4BbswXY2SNPQCn5Sg","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"• Metabolismo: Degradación proteolítica.","guid":"rJiV72LjjTGJhj2l49FGGA","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"13","text":"• Eliminación: Excreción renal y hepática.","guid":"lMPk-ovBWTnKJFcVEb30hA","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"0","text":"3. Presentaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"• Tirzepatida (Laboratorio: Lilly).","guid":"WAWJdGZmlirdlcWKFBqJ1Q","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"• Dosis objetivo: 15 mg/sem.","guid":"vt8Wcj_dPjB2X_QfBIkQfw","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"• Precio mensual en Chile: Aproximadamente $350,000 CLP.","guid":"ZeviZAAbYGagoBvaDg4sMw","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"• Consideraciones de ajuste: No se requiere ajuste en VFG ≥30 ml/min;\\Nno recomendado en insuficiencia hepática grave (Child-Pugh C).","guid":"ib-8V5Ok_0R-odU4_M-UvQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"0","text":"3.1 Mecanismo de\\NAcción de Tirzepatida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Péptido multi-funcional.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"• Modificación de la secuencia peptídica de GIP para unirse a receptores de GIP y GLP-1.","guid":"_s4WnTcHodh0SECOQOQVIQ","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"• Péptido lineal de 39 aminoácidos con una porción de diácido graso C20.","guid":"2cfUUBudFkiPn8FBB1Yvgw","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"• Vida media: ≈ 5 días (116.7 h) → dosis semanal.","guid":"6GoEWuApz9_-uTPuVh51yg","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"• Afinidad similar al GIP nativo y ligeramente menor para GLP-1 nativo.","guid":"kBm0xd91BZv0I5avWR9zqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"0","text":"3.2 Efectividad Terapéutica en Control de\\NGlucemia y Reducción de Peso:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Programa de ensayos\\Nclínicos SURPASS:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"• Efectividad verificada en control glucémico y reducción de peso.","guid":"Iy4dtSBy1cS9By-Ge9iU0w","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"• Dosis inicial: 2.5 mg/sem, aumentando 2.5 mg cada 4 semanas hasta dosis de mantenimiento (5, 10, 15 mg/sem).","guid":"xl2caZn-F87OV68rys6HYA","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"• Reducción de HbA1c (SURPASS 1-5): 1.69% - 2.58%.","guid":"n8UQWUD1mGh15HnyPm2Ing","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"• Reducción de peso corporal (SURPASS 1-5): 5.4 - 11.7 kg.","guid":"0lJDdS5bm9n64GP8u4dXwQ","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"30","text":"• Más de 1 año para estabilizar peso tras iniciar tratamiento.","guid":"-2qkeBMaLQtW9TIp2IossQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"0","text":"3.3 Efectividad y\\NSeguridad Cardiorrenal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"• SURPASS-1 y -2:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Reducción significativa de triglicéridos (18.5% - 24.8%), LDL-C (5.2% - 12.4%), y VLDL-C (17.5% - 23.7%).","guid":"rNxqinxHyBoPE21STq9Z3Q","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"• Aumento significativo de HDL-C (3.2% - 7.9%).","guid":"PSPdS7OGKIrI63pOFYTcvQ","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"• Reducción de PA sistólica (5-6 mmHg), mayor que con semaglutida.","guid":"R5I19FXOFjSPaM0lWF4tGA","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"36","text":"• SURPASS-4:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Efecto sobre eventos\\Ncardiovasculares:","guid":"IVPV-Qs1m7vDK7O_inCZsA","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• ↓ HbA1c > que glargina.","guid":"jat1fW5sD-ULv4Dpr8lV7Q","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"• Menor incidencia de hipoglucemia en 52 semanas.","guid":"iMMCEg5ylBinxNxEGAIRlQ","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"• No asociado con aumento de riesgo cardiovascular.","guid":"pSrhynlb8bWfxVD2TZZ7EQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"36","text":"• Ensayo clínico dedicado en\\Ncurso (SURPASS CVOT):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• Comparación de tirzepatida vs. dulaglutida.","guid":"Xy7f_3T0Lz7-T_-7nFRQkg","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"• Resultados en 2024.","guid":"9_iZ2EXPrePUH70yQHNtsw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"3.4 Indicaciones Futuras\\NMás Allá del T2DM:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Estudio de obesidad\\N(SURMOUNT-1):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Pérdida de peso mayor en individuos sin T2DM.","guid":"39tvFTLikYYY6gYob0WENw","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"• Reducción de 15% - 20.9% en peso con 5-15 mg/sem.","guid":"_NC4Q5sEpG-iVxbkgBxtKA","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"• Efectos adversos: náuseas, diarrea, vómitos, constipación.","guid":"hwFLtzBSimY4Pqiw7T1vUA","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"49","text":"• SURMOUNT-2\\N(Obesidad en T2DM):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"• Reducción de peso 12.8% - 14. 7% con 10-15 mg/sem.","guid":"qOF646jroaGiqbcCC8HxJA","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"54","text":"• Resultados mejores que semaglutida SC 2.4 mg/sem y liraglutida 3.0 mg/día.","guid":"HnRFUH5BmmZNcFUSPnGIuw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"0","text":"4. Estudios clínicos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• SURPASS-2:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"• Año: 2021.","guid":"i4K78AVXgCLJl6gXPpPyBA","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"• País: Multinacional.","guid":"tw4qC3CiNsbbFzKX6EtCVQ","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"• Participantes: 1879.","guid":"lLZJc96u4A-R25e6h4SS8g","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"58","text":"• Características: DM2 inadecuadamente controlada con metformina.","guid":"zXnOAM1CdU9gin6GD7QoEQ","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"58","text":"• Metodología: Randomizado, doble ciego, controlado.","guid":"szLD9CVw2cTLR5hz8o8TFA","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"57","text":"• Endpoints:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• Primarios: Cambio en HbA1c.","guid":"mEpej8rHDe8-jGEXGyKbjQ","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Secundarios: Pérdida de peso, eventos CV.","guid":"P6Ft3IN8X_5BsI4eE3VYQg","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"57","text":"• Significancia: Reducción significativa en HbA1c y peso vs. semaglutida.","guid":"sMDA4llJSUc7zxxtq2JXPA","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"57","text":"• Críticas: Duración a medio plazo, seguimiento CV prolongado requerido.","guid":"qYdNNiUNK1a8of3wJQiY2w","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"5. Consideraciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"• Contraindicaciones: Neoplasia tiroidea medular, MEN 2, hipersensibilidad.","guid":"Rwn-7hr-LGUZaZGlK3QAHg","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"• Consideraciones: Riesgo de hipoglucemia con insulina/SU, pancreatitis (raro).","guid":"6NQDkpV7yqStkgR_Dj3BhQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"0","text":"6. Reacciones\\Nadversas:","guid":"3DGdfJizY-CpticrdIUq5g","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Frecuentes (>10%): Náuseas (12%), diarrea (9%).","guid":"vYtDdWpaNKSfdN4PEFjjyA","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Moderadas (1-10%): Vómitos (5%), hipoglucemia (3%).","guid":"xiVgB4WABlZJDHpjuChebw","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• Raras (<1%): Pancreatitis, hipersensibilidad.","guid":"V50MSjFzs76pW29rrBE7bA","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":75,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"AgonistaDualdeGLP-1yGIP(Tirzepatida)-2024","id":"map_522","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"AgonistaDualdeGLP-1yGIP(Tirzepatida)-2024"}